items.title: Awesome Fiber
items.content_text:
### ‚öôÔ∏è Middlewares / üß¨ Core

*   [BasicAuth (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/basicauth) - Basic auth middleware provides an HTTP basic authentication. It calls the next handler for valid credentials and 401 Unauthorized for missing or invalid credentials.
*   [Cache (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/cache) - Intercept and cache responses.
*   [CORS (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/cors) - Enable cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) with various options.
*   [CSRF (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/csrf) - Protect from CSRF exploits.
*   [Encrypt Cookie (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/encryptcookie) - Encrypt middleware which encrypts cookie values.
*   [ETag (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/etag) - ETag middleware that lets caches be more efficient and save bandwidth, as a web server does not need to resend a full response if the content has not changed.
*   [Expvar (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/expvar) - Expvar middleware that serves via its HTTP server runtime exposed variants in the JSON format.
*   [Favicon (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/favicon) - Ignore favicon from logs or serve from memory if a file path is provided.
*   [FileSystem (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/filesystem) - FileSystem middleware for Fiber, special thanks and credits to Alireza Salary.
*   [Limiter (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/limiter) - Rate-limiting middleware. Use to limit repeated requests to public APIs and/or endpoints such as password reset.
*   [Logger (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/logger) - HTTP request/response logger.
*   [Monitor (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/monitor) - Monitor middleware that reports server metrics, inspired by express-status-monitor.
*   [Pprof (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/pprof) - Pprof middleware that serves via its HTTP server runtime profiling data in the format expected by the pprof visualization tool.
*   [Proxy (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/proxy) - Allows you to proxy requests to a multiple servers.
*   [Recover (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/recover) - Recover middleware recovers from panics anywhere in the stack chain and handles the control to the centralized ErrorHandler.
*   [RequestID (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/requestid) - Adds a requestid to every request.
*   [Session (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/session) - Session middleware. NOTE: This middleware uses our Storage package.
*   [Skip (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/skip) - Skip middleware that skips a wrapped handler is a predicate is true.
*   [Timeout (‚≠ê37k)](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/tree/master/middleware/timeout) - Adds a max time for a request and forwards to ErrorHandler if it is exceeded.

### ‚öôÔ∏è Middlewares / üîó External

*   [storage (‚≠ê298)](https://github.com/gofiber/storage) - Premade storage drivers that implement the Storage interface, designed to be used with various Fiber middlewares.
*   [template (‚≠ê294)](https://github.com/gofiber/template) - This package contains 8 template engines that can be used with Fiber v1.10.x Go version 1.13 or higher is required.

### ‚öôÔ∏è Middlewares / ‚Äçüíª Contrib

*   [fibersentry (‚≠ê262)](https://github.com/gofiber/contrib/tree/main/fibersentry) - Sentry support for Fiber.
*   [fiberzap (‚≠ê262)](https://github.com/gofiber/contrib/tree/main/fiberzap) - Zap logging support for Fiber.
*   [otelfiber (‚≠ê262)](https://github.com/gofiber/contrib/tree/main/otelfiber) - OpenTelemetry support for Fiber.
*   [paseto (‚≠ê262)](https://github.com/gofiber/contrib/tree/main/paseto) - PASETO returns a Web Token (PASETO) auth middleware.
*   [swagger (‚≠ê262)](https://github.com/gofiber/contrib/tree/main/swagger) - Swagger middleware for Fiber. The middleware handles Swagger UI.

### üìÅ Recipes / üå± Third Party

*   [gofiber/recipes (‚≠ê3.3k)](https://github.com/gofiber/recipes) - Official Fiber cookbook.

### üõ†Ô∏è Tools / üå± Third Party

*   [go-dawn/dawn (‚≠ê19)](https://github.com/go-dawn/dawn) - Dawn is an opinionated web framework that provides rapid development capabilities which on top of Fiber.
*   [tompston/gomakeme (‚≠ê11)](https://github.com/tompston/gomakeme) - Generate boilerplate + endpoints for Fiber or Gin REST APIs.

### üìñ Articles / üå± Third Party

*   [Go Fiber by Examples: How can the Fiber Web Framework be useful?](https://dev.to/koddr/go-fiber-by-examples-how-can-the-fiber-web-framework-be-useful-487a)
*   [Build a RESTful API on Go: Fiber, PostgreSQL, JWT and Swagger docs in isolated Docker containers](https://dev.to/koddr/build-a-restful-api-on-go-fiber-postgresql-jwt-and-swagger-docs-in-isolated-docker-containers-475j)
*   [Getting started with Fiber](https://dev.to/fenny/getting-started-with-fiber-36b6)
*   [Fiber v1.9.6 How to improve performance by 817% and stay fast, flexible and friendly?](https://dev.to/koddr/fiber-v1-9-5-how-to-improve-performance-by-817-and-stay-fast-flexible-and-friendly-2dp6)
*   [Create a travel list app with Go, Fiber, Angular, MongoDB and Google Cloud Secret Manager](https://blog.yongweilun.me/create-a-travel-list-app-with-go-fiber-angular-mongodb-and-google-cloud-secret-manager-ck9fgxy0p061pcss1xt1ubu8t)
*   [Is switching from Express to Fiber worth it?](https://dev.to/koddr/are-sure-what-your-lovely-web-framework-running-so-fast-2jl1)
*   [Fiber v1.8. What's new, updated and re-thinked?](https://dev.to/koddr/fiber-v1-8-what-s-new-updated-and-re-thinked-339h)
*   [Fiber released v1.7! What's new and is it still fast, flexible and friendly?](https://dev.to/koddr/fiber-v2-is-out-now-what-s-new-and-is-he-still-fast-flexible-and-friendly-3ipf)
